item.title: The Autobiography of Malcolm x
item.description: “Each day I live as if I am already dead, and I tell you what I would like for you to do. When I am dead - I say it that way because of the things I know, I do not expect to live long enough to read this book in its finished form - I want you to watch and see if I’m not right in what I say: that the white man, in his press, is going to identify me with ‘hate’…
